6/30/2013 @ 5:45pm: If your shooting range has ammo restrictions, this XM193 will pass the "magnet test." I know it is difficult to believe, but our Second Amendment-respecting Obamination of a President canceled funding for the Federal Flight Deck Officer Program (FFDO). That has caused more than a few airlines pilots to sell their HKs. 

Most people know my mantra: "You can buy a better pistol than a Glock, but you're going to have to pay a GREAT amount of money." Well, here's your chance to get better than a Glock for a LITTLE more money! It's a very well cared-for HK USP .40c ("Compact").
This USP .40c was carried in a pilots leather flight bag with his charts and books, so it exhibits some mild, external wear on two high-points-- the edges of the TRITIUM NIGHT SIGHTS and the slide release lever.

The HK USP is the Mercedes Benz of the personal protection/tactical league. They are dependable, durable, fine machines--both ergonomically and mechanically. This pistol fits one's hand and possesses a natural point-of-aim like no other.

I completely stripped this pistol and it is 99% internally and 95% externally (as previously described). Here is your opportunity to own an HK USP Compact that has been correctly broken in at a fraction of the "New Car" cost.

USP COMPACT
The HK USP Compact is a small frame pistol capable of firing the most powerful cartridges in 9 mm, .40 S&W, .45 ACP, and .357 SIG (by special order). Based on the full-size USP models, these handy pistols combine compact size with optimum effective shooting performance.

USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot "two-finger grip" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floorplates. This makes the pistol easy to shoot without sacrificing concealability.

Like their large frame predecessors, USP Compacts are designed with the demanding needs of the law enforcement and military shooters in mind. Using a modified linkless Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high-energy +P loads.

To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. Service life is still engineered to exceed 20,000 rounds.

Easy to shoot, simple to maintain; the USP Compact is a reliable, safe, accurate, and highly concealable pistol.

title: For Sale:  SCAMS. folks please flag there adds. Armslist has no room for scams.FLAG THEM!
postcontent:
listings that that contain location as NEVADA,NEVADA and not a specific location are most likely 95% chance that they are a fraudulent sale of a firearm that does not exist. 

Do your research folks and check the going rate for all firearms. rifles and pistols that are listed on this website for half of what they should go for are most likely a scam.How ever good deals do exist. 

remember face to face transactions are the best way to go. Mailing checks to private address/persons for gun purchases is not wise. Use a FFL Dealer

when buying out of state transactions should be done VIA FFL to FFL and is the law.No  one person can just put a Firearm(registered receiver/chassis)  in the mail without first obtaining an FFL. 

Also most of these recent adds have been constructed using pictures and information off of other websites. Beware !

please contact your local Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives Office for more information on local laws and regulations regarding Firearms sales and transactions.
